

## üíª 1. Controller/PageModel Layer (C# Code)



### Action Results (ASP.NET Core MVC & Web API)

Action Methods in Controllers typically return an implementation of `IActionResult` to define the HTTP response.

| Function/Method               | Type                     | Purpose                     |
| :---------------------------- | :----------------------- | :-------------------------- |
| `return View(model)`          | `ViewResult`             | Returns an HTML view, optionally passing a model object to the view. |
| `return Ok(data)`             | `OkObjectResult`         | Returns an HTTP 200 (OK) status code, typically with JSON data (common in APIs). |
| `return NotFound()`           | `NotFoundResult`         | Returns an HTTP 404 (Not Found) status code. |
| `return BadRequest(error)`    | `BadRequestObjectResult` | Returns an HTTP 400 (Bad Request) status code, often with validation errors. |
| `return RedirectToAction(...)`| `RedirectToActionResult` | Redirects the user's browser to another action method within the application. |
| `return RedirectToPage(...)`  | `RedirectToPageResult`   | Redirects to a different Razor Page (used in Razor Pages). |
| `return Json(data)`           | `JsonResult`             | Returns data serialized as JSON (useful for AJAX calls). |

### Request/Model State Functions

These are properties or methods used within the Controller/PageModel to manage data and validate inputs.

| Property/Method               | Context              | Purpose                       |
| :---------------------------- | :------------------- | :---------------------------- |
| `ModelState.IsValid`          | Controller/PageModel | A boolean property that checks if the incoming data model passed all validation rules (based on Data Annotations). |
| `[HttpGet]` / `[HttpPost]`    | Attributes           | Decorates action methods to specify which HTTP verb they handle (GET for viewing, POST for submitting forms). |
| `[Bind("Prop1,Prop2")]`       | Attribute            | Restricts the properties of a model that the model binder can populate from the request, preventing over-posting. |
| `[ValidateAntiForgeryToken]`  | Attribute            | Ensures a form submission includes a valid anti-forgery token, protecting against Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF). |
| `HttpContext.Session.Set(...)`| Property/Method      | Used to manage session state (storing small amounts of user-specific data server-side). |

** C# SESSION, Method,Description
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Set (String) | "HttpContext.Session.SetString(key, value)" | Stores a string value.
Set (Int)    | "HttpContext.Session.SetInt32(key, value)"  | Stores an integer value.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Get (String) | HttpContext.Session.GetString(key)  | Retrieves a string. Returns null if the key doesn't exist.
Get (Int)    | HttpContext.Session.GetInt32(key)   | Retrieves an integer. Returns null if the key doesn't exist or is not an Int32.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Remove    | HttpContext.Session.Remove(key)  | Removes a specific key-value pair.
Clear All | HttpContext.Session.Clear()      | Removes all keys and values for the current session.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


## üìù 2. Razor View Layer (CSHTML Files)

This is the presentation layer where HTML markup is combined with C# code using the Razor syntax and Tag Helpers.

### Razor Syntax (C# in HTML)

| Syntax     | Purpose             | Example                                              |
| :--------- | :------------------ | :--------------------------------------------------- |
| `@model`   | Directive           | Declares the C# model type passed to the view (e.g., `@model List<Product>`). |
| `@{...}`   | Code Block          | Executes multiple lines of C# code without rendering the output to HTML. |
| `@`        | Implicit Expression | Renders the value of a C# variable or property (e.g., `<p>Hello, @Model.Name</p>`). |
| `@( ... )` | Explicit Expression | Renders the result of a complex C# expression (e.g., `<p>Year: @(DateTime.Now.Year + 1)</p>`). |
| `@inject`  | Directive           | Uses Dependency Injection to access a registered service directly within the view (e.g., `@inject ILogger<T> Logger`). |

### Built-in Tag Helpers (HTML Attributes)

Tag Helpers are C# classes that modify standard HTML elements, making the view syntax cleaner and more intuitive than older HTML Helpers.

| Tag Helper        | Target HTML Element | Common Attributes                               | Purpose                                     |
| :---------------- | :------------------ | :---------------------------------------------- | :------------------------------------------ |
| Anchor            | `<a ... >`          | `asp-controller`, `asp-action`, `asp-route-`    | Generates dynamic URLs for links based on controller actions and route values. |
| Form              | `<form ... >`       | `asp-controller`, `asp-action`, `method="post"` | Generates the form's `action` URL and automatically adds the hidden anti-forgery token. |
| Input             | `<input ... >`      | `asp-for="Model.Property"`                      | Binds the input field to a specific model property, generating `id`, `name`, and validation attributes. |
| Validation        | `<span ... >`       | `asp-validation-for="Property"`                 | Displays the validation message for a specific model property. |
| Validation Summary| `<div ... >`        | `asp-validation-summary="All"`                  | Displays a summary of all model validation errors. |
| Environment       | `<environment ... >`| `include="Development"`                         | Conditionally renders content (like scripts/styles) based on the application's environment. |

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è 3. Startup/Service Configuration Layer (Program.cs/Startup.cs)

These "functions" are primarily extension methods used to set up the framework's core services and the request processing pipeline.

| Function/Method                              | Location     | Purpose                                                                         |
| :------------------------------------------- | :----------- | :------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `builder.Services.AddControllersWithViews()` | `Program.cs` | Registers all the necessary services for using MVC controllers and Razor views. |
| `builder.Services.AddRazorPages()`           | `Program.cs` | Registers services for using the Razor Pages pattern. |
| `builder.Services.AddDbContext<T>(...)`      | `Program.cs` | Registers an Entity Framework Core database context class (`T`) into the Dependency Injection (DI) container. |
| `builder.Services.AddSingleton<I, T>()`      | `Program.cs` | Registers a custom service (implementation `T` for interface `I`) with a Singleton lifetime (one instance for the entire app). |
| `app.UseRouting()`                           | `Program.cs` | Marks where route matching should take place in the HTTP request pipeline. |
| `app.UseAuthentication()`                    | `Program.cs` | Adds the middleware that checks for a user's identity. |
| `app.MapControllerRoute(...)`                | `Program.cs` | Defines the default routing pattern for MVC (e.g., `{controller}/{action}/{id}`). |
